dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Image_Observation_Information
class.description: This class contains observation information for image data.

class.title: Mission_Information
class.description: This class contains information about the Hayabusa2 mission. The attributes in this class are common to all mission data products.

class.title: ONC_Band_Information
class.description: This class contains information of each band for co-registered data.

class.title: ONC_Calibration_Data_Information

class.title: ONC_Image_Information
class.description: This class contains ONC-specific image observation information.

class.title: ONC_Image_Processing_Parameters

class.title: ONC_Instrument_Attributes
class.description: This class contains ONC instrument-specific parameters.

class.title: ONC_Multiband_Observation_Information

class.title: Observation_Geometry

class.title: Sub_Image_Information
class.description: This class contains ONC sub image parameters.

attribute.title: actual_bitdepth
attribute.description: This attribute describes the actual bit-depth for each pixel. This value corresponds to a dynamic range of the raw (l2a) image for ONC. Although the l2a data is stored in a 16-bit integer image array, the bit depth used for nominal image acquisition is 12. A bit depth is reduced to 10 or 8 bit for some images during digital processing in DE or ONC-E dividing the original data by 2 or 4.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: 10-bit
12-bit
8-bit

attribute.title: band_center
attribute.description: This attribute describes the effective band center of the selected band and/or the camera. For the ONC image, this value is calculated using the system efficiency of the specific camera and/or the band, and this value is used to calculate the sensitivity and the effective solar irradiance utilized in the creation of the l2c and the l2d products.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: bandwidth
attribute.description: This attribute describes the effective band with of the selected band and/or the camera. For the ONC image, this value is calculated using the system efficiency of the specific camera and/or the band, and this value is used to calculate the sensitivity and the effective solar irradiance utilized in the creation of the l2c and the l2d products.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: exposure_duration
attribute.description: This attribute describes the exposure time of the observation in units of seconds. When the number of sub images is 2 for ONC image, this value is for the main image. When the number of sub images is more than 2 for ONC image, this value indicates an exposure time for each image.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: filter_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the name of the filter that was used during the observation to select or modify the radiation that was transmitted to the detector. The value 'None' indicates that no filter was used. The possible values are None, No. 1: 390 nm, No. 2: Wide, No. 3: 550 nm, No. 4: 700 nm, No. 5: 860 nm, No. 6: 589 nm, No. 7: 950 nm, and No. 8: 480 nm.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value means the ul-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the wide-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the v-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the w-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the x-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the Na-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the p-band filter of ONC-T is used.
This value means the b-band filter of ONC-T is used.
No filter is used.

attribute.title: image_processing_return_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the return status of the image processing onboard. The possible values are Normal End, Parameter Error, Buffer Size Error, Hardware Operation Error, Overflow, Underflow, Overflow and Underflow, Zero Division, and Operation Interruption.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value means that error related to the buffer size occurred, e.g., image sizes of two buffers specified by two operands of image processing command differ, buffer sizes of source and destination buffers differ.
This value means that error on hardware operation occurred, e.g., memory race condition, hardware operation does not finished until prescribed duration (timeout).
Onboard image processing is completed normally.
This value means that the image processing was interrupted for some reason.
This value means that arithmetic overflow occurred during the image processing.
This value means that both of arithmetic overflow and arithmetic underflow occurred during the image processing.
This value means that invalid arguments have been passed to image processing command which is sent to DE or ONC-E.
This value means that arithmetic underflow occurred during the image processing.
This value means that zero division occurred during the image processing.

attribute.title: number_of_binning
attribute.description: This attribute describes the size of the area used for the onboard binning. For example, if this value is 1, no binning was conducted. If this value is 2, the area of 2 x 2 pixels is binned to one pixel. The possible values are 1, 2, 4, and 8.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No-binning
2 x 2 pixels binning
4 x 4 pixels binning
8 x 8 pixels binning

attribute.title: unit_count_value
attribute.description: This attribute describes the value at the current product corresponding to unit count at the raw data, i.e., the l2a product. This value indicates resolution of the value.

attribute.title: mission_phase_id
attribute.description: This attribute describes the mission phase identifier. The possible values are commissioning, edvega, earth_swing-by, transfer, approach, proximity, return, and reentry.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This identifier is associated with the Approach Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Commissioning Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Earth Swing-by Phase.
This identifier is associated with the EDVEGA Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Asteroid Proximity Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Reentry Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Return Phase.
This identifier is associated with the Transfer Phase.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the mission phase name. The possible values are Commissioning Phase, EDVEGA Phase, Earth Swing-by Phase, Transfer Phase, Approarch Phase, Asteroid Proximity Phase, Return Phase, and Reentry Phase.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2018-06-03T05:59:00Z to 2018-06-27T00:35:00Z.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2018-06-27T00:35:00Z to 2019-11-13T01:00:00Z.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2014-12-03T04:22:04Z to 2015-03-03T00:00:00Z.

This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2015-03-03T00:00:00Z to 2015-10-01T00:00:00Z. EDVEGA is the acronym of Electric Delta-V Earth Gravity Assist which means accelerating spacecraft (delta-V) using electric propulsion and Earth swing-by.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2015-10-01T00:00:00Z to 2015-12-22T14:10:00Z.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2020-10-22T00:00:00Z to 2020-12-05T08:00:00Z.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2019-11-13T01:00:00Z to 2020-10-22T00:00:00Z.
This is the name of mission phase that period is from 2015-12-22T14:10:00Z to 2018-06-03T05:59:00Z.

attribute.title: flat_field_lamp_a_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the flat field (FF) lamp A for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. FF lamp A and B are attached in front of the ONC-T lens system for calibration. The possible values are Off, Low, and High. If the value is Off, the lamp A is off, and if the value is Low or High, the lamp A is on and the voltage mode is set to low or high, respectively.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is high.
The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is low.

attribute.title: normalization_status

attribute.title: dynamic_range
attribute.description: This attribute describes the full dynamic range of pixel value at the center of the field-of-view, that is 4095 DN - bias in the l2a product, where bias is typically about 300 DN in the l2a product. A dynamic range of pixel value at other place on the detector is less than the value at the center of the field-of-view because of the vignetting effect. When the linearity correction is not conducted, values between the linearity_guaranteed_range attribute and this value are not trustworthy. The unit of this attribute depends on a kind of the product.

attribute.title: first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light
attribute.description: This attribute describes the rotation angle around the spacecraft +Y-axis from the reference spacecraft attitude which has the spacecraft +Z-axis is same as the Sun-direction vector. This angle is utilized to define the magnitude of the radiator stray light in the ONC-T image. When the value of the second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute is larger than -7 degrees and the value of the first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute is smaller than -5 degrees, the radiator stray light in the ONC-T image exceeds 1 count per second.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: linearity_guaranteed_range
attribute.description: This attribute describes the maximum value of the linearity guaranteed range at the center of the field-of-view. This value corresponds to about 3100 counts at the center of the field-of-view in the l2a product. A maximum value of the linearity guaranteed range at other pixels on the detector is less than the value at the center of the field-of-view because of the vignetting effect. The values less than this value are trustworthy even if the nonlinearity correction is not conducted.

attribute.title: number_of_subimage
attribute.description: This attribute describes the number of sub images used to create image onboard. For the ONC-T image, typical numbers are 1 for a raw image, 2 for a onboard smear reduction image, and more than 2 for onboard stacking image.

attribute.title: observation_mode
attribute.description: This attribute describes the observation mode. If the value is Science, the image is acquired for the scientific purpose. Such images are basically used to be applied science product procedure (Level 2a and later). If the value is Navigation Dump, the image is acquired for the navigation purpose.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The observation mode is for the navigation, and the image acquired is called navigation dump.
The observation mode is for the scientific observation.

attribute.title: second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light
attribute.description: This attribute describes the rotation angle around the spacecraft +Z-axis from the spacecraft attitude after the rotation around the spacecraft +Y-axis of the value of the first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute from the reference spacecraft attitude which has the spacecraft +Z-axis is same as the Sun-direction vector. This angle is utilized to define the magnitude of the radiator stray light in the ONC-T image. When the value of the second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute is larger than -7 degrees and the value of the first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute is smaller than -5 degrees, the radiator stray light in the ONC-T image exceeds 1 count per second.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: stray_light_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes whether stray light from the backward space of ONC-T exists or not. This value is only applied to the ONC-T image. This value is estimated from the values of the first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute, the second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute, and the empirical formula written in the SIS. See Suzuki+2018, Tatsumi+2019, and/or the SIS for the details. If the value is Affected, this image is estimated as affected by stray light from the backside of the camera, and if the value is Not Affected, this image is estimated as not affected by it.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This image is estimated as affected.
This image is estimated as not affected.

attribute.description: This attribute describes the file name of the flat field that is the dependent component with the CCD temperature. This calibration is only applied to the ONC-T image with x- or p-filters.

attribute.title: temperature_dependent_flat_field_correction_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the correction status of the CCD temperature dependent component of the flat-field. This calibration is only applied to the ONC-T image with x- or p-filters.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The correction of the CCD-temperature dependent component of the flat-field is applied.
The correction of the CCD-temperature dependent component of the flat-field is not applied.

attribute.title: bus_line_voltage
attribute.description: This attribute describes the bus line voltage. This value is estimated by the interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: fla_c_electric_current
attribute.description: This attribute describes the FLA-C (the capacitor bank of the flash lamp) current. This value is estimated by the interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: fla_c_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the FLA-C temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: onc_analog_electronics_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-AE temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: onc_electric_current
attribute.description: This attribute describes the current in the ONC instrument. This value is estimated by the interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: t_ccd_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-T CCD temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: t_electric_circuit_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-T electric circuit temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: t_optics_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-T optics temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w1_ccd_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W1 CCD temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w1_electric_circuit_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W1 electric circuit temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w1_optics_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W1 optics temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w2_ccd_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W2 CCD temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w2_electric_circuit_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W2 electric circuit temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: w2_optics_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the ONC-W2 optics temperature. This value is estimated by interpolation in time at the value of the observation_date_time attribute from the house keeping data.

attribute.title: alignment_offset_correction_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the alignment offset correction. This value is only valid for the product that is equal to or higher than the l2c product.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The alignment offset correction is conducted.
The alignment offset correction is not conducted.

attribute.title: backplane_data_version
attribute.description: This attribute describes the version of backplane data.

attribute.title: backplane_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the backplane file name.

attribute.title: backplane_shape_model_spice_kernel_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the name of the SPICE DSK file which contains the necessary shape model to create backplane data for the photometric correction required to create the l2e product.

attribute.title: backplane_spice_kernel_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the SPICE kernel file name used to calculate the backplanes such as longitude, latitude, and viewing geometories of Ryugu using the shape model specified by the backplane_shape_model_spice_kernel_file_name attribute.

attribute.title: distance_to_ryugu_at_center
attribute.description: This attribute describes the distance to the surface of Ryugu at the center of the image.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: distortion_correction_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the distortion correction. This value is only valid for the product that is equal to or higher than the l2c product.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The distortion correction is applied.
The distortion correction is not applied.

attribute.title: reference_frame_date_time
attribute.description: This attribute describes the reference observation time of the reference image frame in UTC.

attribute.title: reference_frame_filter_axis_number
attribute.description: This attribute describes the filter axis number of the reference image frame.

attribute.title: reference_frame_filter_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the filter name of the reference image frame.

attribute.title: spatial_resolution_of_ryugu_at_center
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spatial resolution of the Ryugu's surface at the center of the image.

attribute.title: stray_light_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes whether stray light from the backward space of ONC-T exists or not. This value is only applied to the ONC-T image. This value is estimated from the values of the first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute, the second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light attribute, and the empirical formula written in the SIS. See Suzuki+2018, Tatsumi+2019, and/or the SIS for the details. If the value is Affected, this image is estimated as affected by stray light from the backside of the camera, and if the value is Not Affected, this image is estimated as not affected by it.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This image is estimated as affected.
This image is estimated as not affected.

attribute.title: backplane_data_version
attribute.description: This attribute describes the version of backplane data.

attribute.title: backplane_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the backplane file name.

attribute.title: backplane_shape_model_spice_kernel_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the name of the SPICE DSK file which contains the necessary shape model to create backplane data for the photometric correction required to create the l2e product.

attribute.title: backplane_spice_kernel_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the SPICE kernel file name used to calculate the backplanes such as longitude, latitude, and viewing geometories of Ryugu using the shape model specified by the backplane_shape_model_spice_kernel_file_name attribute.

attribute.title: earth_distance_from_spacecraft
attribute.description: This attribute describes the distance between the center of the spacecraft and the center of Earth.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: ryugu_distance_from_spacecraft
attribute.description: This attribute describes the distance between the center of the spacecraft and the center of Ryugu.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: spacecraft_x_position
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spacecraft x-position from the Sun in the J2000 coordinate system. This value is calculated without light time correction nor stellar aberration.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: spacecraft_y_position
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spacecraft y-position from the Sun in the J2000 coordinate system. This value is calculated without light time correction nor stellar aberration.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: spacecraft_z_position
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spacecraft z-position from the Sun in the J2000 coordinate system. This value is calculated without light time correction nor stellar aberration.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: spatial_resolution_of_ryugu_at_center
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spatial resolution of the Ryugu's surface at the center of the image.

attribute.title: sun_direction_spacecraft_x_axis_angle
attribute.description: This attribute describes the angle of the spacecraft's x-axis and the Sun direction.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: sun_direction_spacecraft_y_axis_angle
attribute.description: This attribute describes the angle of the spacecraft's y-axis and the Sun direction.

attribute.title: naif_instrument_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the NAIF name of the instrument.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Hayabusa2 LIDAR is used.
Hayabusa2 NIRS3 is used.
Hayabusa2 ONC-T is used.
Hayabusa2 ONC-W1 is used.
Hayabusa2 ONC-W2 is used.
Hayabusa2 TIR is used.

attribute.title: observation_date_time
attribute.description: This attribute describes the reference observation time in UTC.

attribute.title: observation_start_date_time
attribute.description: This attribute describes the start time of the observation in UTC.

attribute.title: observation_stop_date_time
attribute.description: This attribute describes the stop time of the observation in UTC.

attribute.title: raw_file_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the file name of the raw data in level 0 that is the source of this file.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the start time of the observation expressed in the spacecraft clock count.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the stop time of the observation expressed in the spacecraft clock count.

attribute.title: analog_electronics_mode
attribute.description: This attribute describes the mode of ONC-AE, ONC analogue data processing unit. The possible values are Standby and Shot.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The mode is Shot.
The mode is Standby.

attribute.title: digital_electronics_selection
attribute.description: This attribute describes which digital electronics, either of ONC-E or DE is selected for processing of the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. Basically, DE is selected for digital processing for the scientific purpose, whereas ONC-E is selected for the optical navigation. The possible values are DE and ONC-E.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: DE (Digital Electronics) is used for digital data processing.
ONC-E is used for digital data processing.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_driving_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the driving status of the ONC-T filter wheel driver for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The filter wheel driver is driving.
The filter wheel driver is stopped.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_null_position_flag
attribute.description: This attribute describes the filter wheel driver null position flag for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The null point of the filter wheel is detected.
The null point of the filter wheel is not detected.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_position_sensor_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the filter wheel position sensor for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The filter wheel position sensor is off.
The filter wheel position sensor is on.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_reset_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes whether the filter wheel driver is in reset sequence or not for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The filter wheel driver is in reset sequence.
The filter wheel driver is not in reset sequence.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_step_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the step count of the filter wheel driver for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_counter. This value increases every 1/4800 rotation, thus this value increases 4800 after one filter wheel rotation.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_step_counter_error_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the error count of the filter wheel driver step counter.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_timeout_error_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the filter wheel driver timeout error count in 4 bits for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

attribute.title: flash_lamp_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the flash lamp for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. The flash lamp is attached to illuminate the target marker(s) for the ONC-W1 image. This value is usually set to be "Disable", and is switched to "Enable" for the target marker tracking.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The flash lamp is off for the imaging.
The flash lamp is on for the imaging.

attribute.title: flat_field_lamp_a_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of the flat field (FF) lamp A for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. FF lamp A and B are attached in front of the ONC-T lens system for calibration. The possible values are Off, Low, and High. If the value is Off, the lamp A is off, and if the value is Low or High, the lamp A is on and the voltage mode is set to low or high, respectively.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is high.
The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is low.
The lamp A is off.

attribute.title: flat_field_lamp_b_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the status of flat field (FF) lamp B for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. FF lamp A and B are attached in front of the ONC-T lens system for calibration.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lamp B is on, and the voltage mode is high.
The lamp B is on, and the voltage mode is low.
The lamp B is off.

attribute.title: sequence_number
attribute.description: This attribute describes the sequence number of a series of sub images.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_count
attribute.description: This attribute describes the spacecraft clock count at the end of image acquisition for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

attribute.title: t_camera_selection_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the selection status of the ONC-T camera head by ONC-AE for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. The possible values are Off (not selected) and On (selcted).

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: ONC-AE does not select the ONC-T camera head for imaging.
ONC-AE selects the ONC-T camera head for imaging.

attribute.title: t_driving_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the driving status of the ONC-T camera head for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. The possible values are Off (not driving) and On (driving).

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The ONC-T camera head does not drive.
The ONC-T camera head drives.

attribute.title: t_exposure_duration
attribute.description: This attribute describes the exposure time in seconds of the ONC-T observation for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. This value is valid when ONC-T is selected as a valid camera, i.e., value of the t_camera_selection_status attribute is "On". The list of values is 0, 0.00544, 0.00820, 0.01088, 0.01640, 0.02176, 0.03280, 0.04352, 0.06560, 0.08704, 0.13120, 0.17408, 0.26240, 0.34816, 0.52480, 0.69632, 1.04960, 1.39264, 2.09920, 2.78528, 4.19840, 5.57056, 8.39680, 11.14112, 16.79360, 22.28224, 33.58720, 44.56448, 67.17440, 89.12896, 134.34880, and 178.25792.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: t_filter_name
attribute.description: This attribute describes the name of the selected filter of ONC-T for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. This value should be neglected when ONC-T is not selected. The possible values are No. 1: 390 nm, No. 2: Wide, No. 3: 550 nm, No. 4: 700 nm, No. 5: 860 nm, No. 6: 589 nm, No. 7: 950 nm, and No. 8: 480 nm.

This value means the wide-band filter is used.
This value means the v-band filter is used.
This value means the w-band filter is used.
This value means the x-band filter is used.
This value means the Na-band filter is used.
This value means the p-band filter is used.
This value means the b-band filter is used.

attribute.title: w1_camera_selection_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the selection status of the ONC-W1 camera head by ONC-AE for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: ONC-AE does not select the ONC-W1 camera head for imaging.
ONC-AE selects the ONC-W1 camera head for imaging.

attribute.title: w1_driving_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the driving status of the ONC-W1 camera head for the n-th image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The ONC-W1 camera head is off.
The ONC-W1 camera head is on.

attribute.title: w1_exposure_duration
attribute.description: This attribute describes the exposure time in seconds for the ONC-W1 observation for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. This values is valid when ONC-W1 is selected as a valid camera, i.e., value of the w1_camera_selection_status attribute is "On". The list of values is 0, 0.00017000, 0.00025625, 0.00034000, 0.00051250, 0.00068000, 0.00102500, 0.00136, 0.00205, 0.00272, 0.00410, 0.00544, 0.00820, 0.01088, 0.01640, 0.02176, 0.03280, 0.04352, 0.06560, 0.08704, 0.13120, 0.17408, 0.26240, 0.34816, 0.52480, 0.69632, 1.04960, 1.39264, 2.09920, 2.78528, 4.19840, and 5.57056.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: w2_camera_selection_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the selection status of the ONC-W2 camera head by ONC-AE for the n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

attribute.description: This attribute describes the driving status of the ONC-W2 camera head for the n-th image, where n is sequence_number.

The list of values is 0, 0.00136, 0.00205, 0.00272, 0.00410, 0.00544, 0.00820, 0.01088, 0.01640, 0.02176, 0.03280, 0.04352, 0.06560, 0.08704, 0.13120, 0.17408, 0.26240, 0.34816, 0.52480, 0.69632, 1.04960, 1.39264, 2.09920, 2.78528, 4.19840, 5.57056, 8.39680, 11.14112, 16.79360, 22.28224, 33.58720, and 44.56448.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: bolometer_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the uncooled micro-bolometer array temperature in the detector package of TIR-S. This is kept at the temperature specified by the peltier_desired_temperature attribute (nominally 40 degrees Celsius) +/- 0.5 degrees Celsius during the observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring the image.

attribute.title: case_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the case temperature of TIR-S. This is kept at constant temperature during the observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring the image.

attribute.title: coarse_grained_temperature_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the coarse-grained temperature status.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The Peltier temperature is not within +- 10 degrees Celsius to the desired value indicated by the peltier_desired_temperature attribute.
The Peltier temperature is within +- 10 degrees Celsius to the desired value indicated by the peltier_desired_temperature attribute.

attribute.title: fine_grained_temperature_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the fine-grained temperature status.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The Peltier temperature is within +- 0.1 degrees Celsius to the desired value indicated by the peltier_desired_temperature attribute.
The Peltier temperature is not within +- 0.1 degrees Celsius to the desired value indicated by the peltier_desired_temperature attribute.

attribute.title: lens_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the lens temperature of TIR-S. The lens of TIR-S is kept at constant temperature during the observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring the image.

attribute.title: number_of_accumulated_images
attribute.description: This attribute describes the scacking frame number of the images. The value should be 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, and 128.

attribute.title: number_of_bit_shift
attribute.description: This attribute describes the number of bit shifts applied to the image onboard. The raw image is the 12-bit data without any bit shifts. The stacked images have bit depth of 16-, 17-, 18-, and 19-bits before the bit shifts, and are applied the bit shift of 1, 2, 3, and 4, respectively, to acquire the data with the bitdepth of 15-bit.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No bit shift is applied.
One bit shift is applied for the 16 frame stacked image.
Two bit shifts are applied for the 32 frame stacked image.
Three bit shifts are applied for the 64 frame stacked image.
Four bit shifts are applied for the 128 frame stacked image.

attribute.title: package_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the detector package temperature of TIR-S. This is kept at constant temperature during the observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring the image.

attribute.title: peltier_desired_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the setting of the desired temprerature by the Peltier temperature controller.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The desired temperature is set to 10 degrees Celsius.
The desired temperature is set to 40 degrees Celsius.

attribute.title: peltier_power_status
attribute.description: This attribute describes the Peltier cooler/heater power status.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Peltier power is off.
Peltier power is on.

attribute.title: shutter_temperature
attribute.description: This attribute describes the shutter temperature of TIR-S. The shutter as a blackbody calibration target of TIR-S is kept at constant temperature during the observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring the image.

attribute.title: tir_image_type
attribute.description: This attribute describes the type of the TIR image.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The target image before the subtraction of the shutter image.
The target image after the subtraction of the shutter image.
The shutter image.
